ray start --address=ray-head:6379 --node-ip-address=\"${MY_POD_IP}\"   --num-cpus=1 --block\n      ```\n\n      ### 1.4 Resource Requests / Limits\n\n      Both `ray-head` and `ray-worker` containers have `resources: {}` — no\n      requests or limits are set.\n\n      ### 1.5 Services\n\n      **ray-head** (ClusterIP: 10.96.82.179):\n\n      | Port Name  | Port | Target Port | Protocol |\n      |------------|------|-------------|----------|\n      | gcs        | 6379 | 6379        | TCP      |\n      | dashboard  | 8265 | 8265        | TCP      |\n\n      No LoadBalancer or NodePort services exist; the dashboard is reachable only\n      within the cluster.\n\n      ---\n\n      ## 2. Proposed Changes for Next Upgrade Window\n\n      ### 2.1 Image Upgrade: 2.9.0 → 2.10.0\n\n      Upgrade both Deployments from `rayproject/ray:2.9.0` to `rayproject/ray:2.10.0`.\n      Ray 2.10 is the next minor release and includes fixes for GCS fault tolerance and\n      dashboard stability.\n\n      **Risk**: Minor — rolling update; workers reconnect automatically after head\n      restarts. Drain any in-flight jobs before upgrading head.\n\n      ### 2.2 Add Resource Requests and Limits\n\n      Currently both containers run with no resource guardrails, which means the\n      scheduler cannot make placement decisions and OOM kills are possible.\n\n      Proposed values (tune to actual node capacity before applying):\n\n      | Container  | CPU Request | CPU Limit | Memory Request | Memory Limit |\n      |------------|-------------|-----------|----------------|--------------|\n      | ray-head   | 500m        | 2000m     | 1Gi            | 2Gi          |\n      | ray-worker | 1000m       | 2000m     | 2Gi            | 4Gi          |\n\n      ### 2.3 Worker Scale-Out: 3 → 5 Replicas\n\n      Scale ray-worker from 3 to 5 replicas to support the next workload tier.\n      Verify node capacity (5 × 1 CPU + 2 Gi memory) before applying.\n\n      ### 2.4 Dashboard Security Hardening\n\n      The dashboard is currently exposed on an unprotected ClusterIP port (8265).\n      Proposal: add a `--dashboard-agent-listen-port` restriction and document that\n      external access must go through an authenticated ingress or kubectl port-forward\n      only. No Service-type change is proposed yet (evaluate after assessing user base).\n\n      ---\n\n      ## 3. Exact kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN — for review only)\n\n      ### Step 1: Upgrade ray-head image and add resource limits\n\n      ```bash\n      kubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-head ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\n      kubectl -n ray set resources deployment/ray-head   --requests='cpu=500m,memory=1Gi'   --limits='cpu=2000m,memory=2Gi'\n      ```\n\n      ### Step 2: Wait for ray-head rollout to complete\n\n      ```bash\n      kubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-head --timeout=300s\n      ```\n\n      ### Step 3: Upgrade ray-worker image and add resource limits\n\n      ```bash\n      kubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-worker ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\n      kubectl -n ray set resources deployment/ray-worker   --requests='cpu=1000m,memory=2Gi'   --limits='cpu=2000m,memory=4Gi'\n      ```\n\n      ### Step 4: Wait for ray-worker rollout to complete\n\n      ```bash\n      kubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-worker --timeout=300s\n      ```\n\n      ### Step 5: Scale ray-worker to 5 replicas\n\n      ```bash\n      kubectl -n ray scale deployment/ray-worker --replicas=5\n      kubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-worker --timeout=120s\n      ```\n\n      ### Step 6: Verify cluster health post-upgrade\n\n      ```bash\n      kubectl -n ray get pods -l app.kubernetes.io/name=ray\n      kubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head ray-worker\n      kubectl -n ray logs -l app.kubernetes.io/component=head --tail=50\n      ```\n\n      ### Rollback (if issues arise)\n\n      ```bash\n      kubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-head\n      kubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-worker\n      kubectl -n ray scale deployment/ray-worker --replicas=3\n      ```\n\n      ---\n\n      ## 4. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\n      - [ ] Confirm no long-running Ray jobs are in-flight (`ray job list` or dashboard)\n      - [ ] Verify node capacity supports 5 workers at proposed resource levels\n      - [ ] Snapshot current Deployment YAMLs:\n            `kubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head ray-worker -o yaml > ray-deploy-backup.yaml`\n      - [ ] Announce maintenance window to cluster users (dashboard downtime ~30s)\n      - [ ] Confirm `rayproject/ray:2.10.0` image is available in the registry\n\n      ---\n\n      ## 5. Post-Upgrade Verification\n\n      - All 5 ray-worker pods reach `Running/Ready` state\n      - ray-head pod reaches `Running/Ready` state with new image\n      - Dashboard accessible on port 8265 (via port-forward)\n      - Ray cluster shows correct node count in dashboard or via:\n        `kubectl -n ray exec -it deploy/ray-head -- ray status`\n  kind: ConfigMap\n  metadata:\n    creationTimestamp: \"2026-06-25T13:36:06Z\"\n    name: change-plan\n    namespace: ray\n    resourceVersion: \"185908\"\n    uid: bafb16b6-5b61-4668-b05c-fd9e3a801f8e\n- apiVersion: v1\n  data:\n    job.py: |\n      import subprocess\n      import socket\n      import time\n      import ray\n\n      my_ip = socket.gethostbyname(socket.gethostname())\n      subprocess.run(\n          [\"ray\", \"start\", \"--address=ray-head:6379\", f\"--node-ip-address={my_ip}\"],\n          check=True,\n          timeout=60,\n      )\n      time.sleep(2)\n\n      ray.init(address=\"auto\")\n      print(\"pong\")\n      ray.shutdown()\n  kind: ConfigMap\n  metadata:\n    annotations:\n      kubectl.kubernetes.io/last-applied-configuration: |\n        {\"apiVersion\":\"v1\",\"data\":{\"job.py\":\"import ray\\n\\nray.init(address=\\\"ray://ray-head:10001\\\")\\n\\nprint(\\\"pong\\\")\\n\\nray.shutdown()\\n\"},\"kind\":\"ConfigMap\",\"metadata\":{\"annotations\":{},\"l