${MY_POD_IP}\"\n            --num-cpus=1 --block\n\nDeviation: The ray-head container's last-applied annotation records\n--include-dashboard=false. The live command has been changed to\n--dashboard-host=0.0.0.0 (dashboard enabled and bound to all interfaces)\nand container port 8265 was added. This is an intentional non-default\nchange evidenced by Deployment generation=2.\n\n---\n\n5. EXPOSED SERVICES\n-------------------\nService: ray-head\n  Type      : ClusterIP\n  ClusterIP : 10.96.82.179\n  Ports:\n    gcs       6379/TCP -> 6379\n    dashboard 8265/TCP -> 8265\n\nDeviation: The dashboard port (8265) is exposed on the Service. The\noriginal last-applied annotation shows only the gcs port (6379). The\ndashboard port was added as a non-default change. The Service type is\nClusterIP only — the dashboard is NOT externally reachable outside the\ncluster without a port-forward or Ingress.\n\nNo LoadBalancer or NodePort services exist in the namespace.\n\n---\n\n6. ACTIVE CONFIGMAPS\n--------------------\nName              | Keys        | Notes\n------------------|-------------|----------------------------------------\nkube-root-ca.crt  | ca.crt      | System-managed cluster CA certificate\nchange-plan       | plan.md     | Team-authored migration plan for next\n                  |             | upgrade window (image 2.9->2.10, resource\n                  |             | limits, scale to 5 workers)\nray-job-script    | job.py      | Ray job submission script. The live\n                  |             | content differs from last-applied: adds\n                  |             | subprocess/socket calls to manually join\n                  |             | the cluster before ray.init(address='auto').\n                  |             | This is a non-default modification.\n\n---\n\n7. DEVIATIONS FROM DEFAULT/BASELINE SUMMARY\n-------------------------------------------\n# | Component          | Parameter           | Baseline/Default      | Current Live Value\n--|--------------------|--------------------|------------------------|--------------------\n1 | ray-worker         | spec.replicas      | 2                      | 3\n2 | ray-head           | dashboard flag     | --include-dashboard=   | --dashboard-host=\n  |                    |                    |   false                |   0.0.0.0\n3 | ray-head Service   | ports              | gcs:6379 only          | gcs:6379 +\n  |                    |                    |                        | dashboard:8265\n4 | ray-head container | resources          | (not set — matches     | resources: {}\n  | ray-worker cont.   |                    | current state)         | (no requests/limits)\n5 | ray-job-script CM  | job.py content     | Simple ray.init via    | Extended script with\n  |                    |                    | ray://ray-head:10001   | subprocess cluster join\n\n---\n\n8. COMPLIANCE NOTES AND RECOMMENDATIONS\n----------------------------------------\n[HIGH] No resource requests or limits set on either container.\n  -> Risk: Unbounded memory/CPU usage; OOM kills possible; scheduler cannot\n     bin-pack correctly. Set requests and limits before the next change window.\n     Suggested values per change-plan: head cpu=500m/2000m mem=1Gi/2Gi;\n     worker cpu=1000m/2000m mem=2Gi/4Gi.\n\n[MEDIUM] Dashboard exposed without authentication (port 8265, ClusterIP).\n  -> The dashboard is reachable by any workload inside the cluster. No\n     authentication or authorization is configured on the Ray dashboard by\n     default. Recommendation: restrict access via NetworkPolicy or route\n     external access only through an authenticated Ingress / kubectl\n     port-forward.\n\n[LOW] ray-job-script ConfigMap modified from last-applied baseline.\n  -> The live job.py uses a manual subprocess-based cluster-join pattern\n     instead of the standard ray:// client connection. This bypasses Ray\n     Client protocol and may not work correctly with all cluster configurations.\n     Review and align